  "voiceover": "\"Jesus was just copied from pagan myths.\" Let's actually check the sources. First — it's not a silly claim. There really are ancient dying-and-rising gods: Osiris, Adonis. The parallels are real. But read the sources. The scholar who debunked this wasn't an apologist — it was Jonathan Z. Smith of the University of Chicago. Those gods die and revive with the crops, every year, in a mythic 'once upon a time.' The Jesus claim is a different kind of thing: a named man, under Pontius Pilate, in a known city, risen once, bodily, for good. And it's early — Paul quotes a creed dated within a few years of the crucifixion. Too early for legend. Not a myth. Something new.",
